### Job Category Controller Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories

### 1. Create a new Job Category
POST http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Software Development",
  "description": "Jobs related to software development and programming",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/software.png",
  "parentId": null
}

### 2. Create a Sub Category
POST http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Backend Development",
  "description": "Backend development roles",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/backend.png",
  "parentId": 1
}

### 3. Create another category
POST http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Data Science",
  "description": "Data science and analytics roles",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/data.png",
  "parentId": null
}

### 4. Get all Job Categories
GET http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories

### 5. Get Job Category by ID
GET http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/1

### 6. Get Job Category by ID (2)
GET http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/2

### 7. Get Job Category by ID (3)
GET http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/3

### 8. Update Job Category (1)
PUT http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Software Development (Updated)",
  "description": "Updated description for software development",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/software-updated.png",
  "parentId": null
}

### 9. Update Job Category (2)
PUT http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Full Stack Development",
  "description": "Full stack development roles",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/fullstack.png",
  "parentId": 1
}

### 10. Delete Job Category (3)
DELETE http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/3

### 11. Get all Job Categories after deletion
GET http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories

### 12. Try to get deleted category (should fail)
GET http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories/3

### 13. Try to create duplicate category (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Software Development (Updated)",
  "description": "This should fail because name already exists",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/duplicate.png",
  "parentId": null
}

### 14. Try to create category with invalid parent (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid Parent Category",
  "description": "Testing invalid parent",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/invalid.png",
  "parentId": 999
}

### 15. Try to create category without name (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8083/api/job-categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "description": "No name provided",
  "iconUrl": "https://example.com/icons/noname.png",
  "parentId": null
}
